# Update changelog

This project keeps a CHANGELOG.md at the repo root following
[Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format.

When invoked:

1. Read CHANGELOG.md. If an `## [Unreleased]` section exists, add to it.
   Otherwise create one at the top, above the most recent released version.
2. Categorize the change under one of:
   - **Added** — new features
   - **Changed** — changes to existing functionality
   - **Deprecated** — soon-to-be removed features
   - **Removed** — removed features
   - **Fixed** — bug fixes
   - **Security** — security-relevant changes
3. Write the entry as one line, past tense, user-facing language. Reference
   issue/PR numbers if known.

Skip the changelog for: internal refactors with no user impact, test-only
changes, dependency bumps unless they change behavior, doc fixes.

If CHANGELOG.md does not exist, create it with the standard header:

```markdown
# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]
```
